658
00:57:38,004 --> 00:57:41,064
How dare... Don't come back!

659
00:57:41,173 --> 00:57:44,165
<i>- Don't worry, May.
- Don't come back!</i>

660
00:57:49,248 --> 00:57:52,115
<i>I bet they'll be back holdin'hands
on the porch swing tomorrow.</i>

661
00:57:52,218 --> 00:57:56,917
I don't know, Lily.
Some people rather die than forgive.

662
00:57:57,023 --> 00:57:59,184
And June is one of'em.

663
00:57:59,292 --> 00:58:03,558
She still hasn't forgiven me for paintin'
the house, and that was 10 years ago.

664
00:58:03,663 --> 00:58:07,155
Well, how come, if your favorite color is blue,
you painted the house so pink?

665
00:58:07,266 --> 00:58:09,598
That was May's doin'.

666
00:58:09,702 --> 00:58:12,102
She was with me the day
I went to the paint store...

667
00:58:12,204 --> 00:58:16,106
and she latched onto this sample
called Caribbean Pink.

668
00:58:16,208 --> 00:58:20,201
Said it made her wanna dance
a Spanish flamenco.

669
00:58:20,313 --> 00:58:23,908
I thought it was the tackiest color
I ever seen in my life.

670
00:58:24,016 --> 00:58:27,884
But if it could lift May's heart,
then I guess she ought to live in it.

671
00:58:27,987 --> 00:58:29,955
Well, that was sure nice of you.

672
00:58:30,056 --> 00:58:33,583
Well, some things
don't matter that much, Lily.

673
00:58:33,693 --> 00:58:36,560
Like the color
of a house and whatnot.

674
00:58:36,662 --> 00:58:39,290
<i>But liftin' someone's heart...
now that matters.</i>

675
00:58:40,800 --> 00:58:44,327
- Were you ever in love?
- Course I was.

676
00:58:44,437 --> 00:58:47,372
