01:25:24,678 --> 01:25:28,239
She had an old friend from high school,
moved to Sylvan.

942
01:25:28,348 --> 01:25:32,375
Told her there were jobs,
and men back from the war.

943
01:25:32,485 --> 01:25:34,453
So she moved.

944
01:25:34,554 --> 01:25:36,613
I think it was 'cause of me though.

945
01:25:36,723 --> 01:25:39,487
I just think she wanted me nearby.

946
01:25:39,593 --> 01:25:44,155
So my mother came to Sylvan,
met T. Ray and got married.

947
01:25:44,264 --> 01:25:46,164
That's right.

948
01:25:46,266 --> 01:25:48,325
But what I don't get
is why she married him.

949
01:25:50,203 --> 01:25:54,867
I think Deborah liked the fact
that he was decorated in the war.

950
01:25:54,975 --> 01:25:56,875
She thought he was brave.

951
01:25:56,977 --> 01:25:59,036
Said he treated her like a princess.

952
01:25:59,145 --> 01:26:01,739
It's not the same T. Ray.
I can tell you that right now.

953
01:26:03,950 --> 01:26:07,442
You know, Lily,
people can start out one way...

954
01:26:07,554 --> 01:26:12,719
<i>and by the time life get through with 'em,
end up completely different.</i>

955
01:26:12,826 --> 01:26:16,922
<i>I mean, I don't doubt that he started off
lovin'her. Fact, he worshipped her.</i>

956
01:26:17,030 --> 01:26:22,229
<i>But after about six months or so,
her love wore off.</i>

957
01:26:22,335 --> 01:26:24,599
But she married him?

958
01:26:24,704 --> 01:26:28,105
<i>But if the love had worn off,
why did she marry him?</i>

959
01:26:30,076 --> 01:26:33,568
Honey, Deborah was pregnant.

960
01:26:33,680 --> 01:26:35,580
That's why.

961
01:26:42,455 --> 01:26:44,423
She called me
soon after you were born.

962
01:26:44,524 --> 01:26:48,426
<i>I got letters and phone calls,
mostly about you.</i>

963
01:26:48,528 --> 01:26:53,124
How you were sittin' up
and takin' your first steps.

964
01:26:53,233 --> 01:26:55,667
<i>Playin'patty-cake.</i>

965
01:26:57,003 --> 01:27:01,337
<i>But then the letters
start comin'less and less.</i>

966
01:27:01,441 --> 01:27:04,001
And one day she called me up...

967
01:27:04,110 --> 01:27:06,977
and she said she was leavin'T. Ray.

968
01:27:07,080 --> 01:27:09,241
- Thank you.
- Yes, ma'am.

969
01:27:09,349 --> 01:27:12,512
<i>When I picked her up
from the bus station...</i>

970
01:27:12,619 --> 01:27:14,519
<i>she didn't even look like herself.</i>

971
01:27:15,789 --> 01:27:17,689
<i>She had gotten so thin.</i>

972
01:27:17,791 --> 01:27:20,885
I was with her when you picked her up
from the bus station, right?

973
01:27:23,296 --> 01:27:25,230
<i>She brought me along, didn't she?</i>

974
01:27:28,668 --> 01:27:31,034
<i>No. She came by herself, honey.</i>

975
01:27:34,808 --> 01:27:37,538
<i>Why?</i>

976
01:27:37,644 --> 01:27:39,544
Why didn't she bring me?

977
01:27:41,848 --> 01:27:45,545
All I know, Lily,
is she was fallin' apart.

978
01:27:45,652 --> 01:27:47,552
Depressed people do things
they wouldn't ordinarily do.

979
01:27:47,654 --> 01:27:51,021
It was easy for her to leave me
'cause she never wanted me in the first place.

980
01:27:51,124 --> 01:27:53,024
Lily.

981
01:27:55,095 --> 01:27:57,928
<i>After she was here
for a few months...</i>

982
01:27:58,031 --> 01:28:01,728
and started feelin' better, she...
she start talkin' about how much she missed you.

983
01:28:03,670 --> 01:28:05,900
Then she went back
to Sylvan to see you.

984
01:28:07,006 --> 01:28:09,600
She was just comin' for her things.

985
01:28:09,709 --> 01:28:13,509
- I believe she came back for you.
- I'm goin' to bed.

986
01:28:13,613 --> 01:28:15,103
<i>Lily!</i>

987
01:28:15,215 --> 01:28:18,343
Now your mama
made a terrible mistake.

988
01:28:18,451 --> 01:28:20,351
But I believe she tried to fix it.

989
01:28:20,453 --> 01:28:22,353
Good night.

990
01:28:27,460 --> 01:28:30,258
Damn it, Deborah.

991
01:28:43,543 --> 01:28:45,101
I hate you!

992
01:28:45,211 --> 01:28:47,805
I hate your guts!

993
01:29:06,599 --> 01:29:09,067
Why didn't you love me?

994
01:30:19,606 --> 01:30:21,506
Tiburon.

995
01:30:25,278 --> 01:30:27,178
Lily.

996
01:30:30,984 --> 01:30:33,214
What in Mary's name happened here?

997
01:30:37,857 --> 01:30:39,757
Answer me.

998
01:30:47,233 --> 01:30:49,724
T. Ray was right about my mother.

999
01:30:51,971 --> 01:30:53,871
She left me.

1000
01:30:59,779 --> 01:31:02,441
<i>Hi.</i>

1001
01:31:02,549 --> 01:31:04,449
Hi.

1002
01:31:04,551 --> 01:31:07,486
I brought some
of your mama's belongings.

1003
01:31:12,685 --> 01:31:16,883
It's just a handful of things your mama left
when she went back to get you.

1004
01:31:19,725 --> 01:31:21,716
Been in this box...

1005
01:31:23,195 --> 01:31:25,390
10 years, I guess.

1006
01:31:27,767 --> 01:31:29,894
You really loved her.

1007
01:31:34,073 --> 01:31:37,474
It was complicated.
But, yes, I did.

1008
01:31:38,577 --> 01:31:41,478
How was it complicated?

1009
01:31:41,580 --> 01:31:43,912
I was her nanny.

1010
01:31:44,016 --> 01:31:47,247
Things were different
in her world than mine.

1011
01:31:49,955 --> 01:31:53,413
We like to think
that love is pure and limitless.

1012
01:31:53,526 --> 01:31:57,792
But love like that
can't exist in a hateful time.

1013
01:32:00,366 --> 01:32:03,199
But she made me love her anyway.

1014
01:32:06,038 --> 01:32:09,701
There is no perfect love, Lily.

1015
01:32:27,059 --> 01:32:29,391
Your mama's pocket mirror.

1016
01:32:31,063 --> 01:32:35,261
If you look in here,
you see your mama looking back at you.

1017
01:32:57,089 --> 01:32:59,023
Well, I'll be.

1018
01:33:05,497 --> 01:33:08,728
She was wearin' that pin
the day she got here.

1019
01:33:25,351 --> 01:33:27,376
There's just one last thing.

1020
01:34:09,228 --> 01:34:11,719
Hey.

1021
01:34:11,830 --> 01:34:13,798
Hey.

1022
01:34:23,876 --> 01:34:25,969
- What happened to you?
- What about it?

1023
01:34:26,078 --> 01:34:28,444
It changed you, didn't it?

1024
01:34:33,419 --> 01:34:37,788
Sometimes, Lily, I...

1025
01:34:37,890 --> 01:34:39,790
I get so angry.

1026
01:34:41,160 --> 01:34:43,390
I just want to kill somethin'.

1027
01:34:43,495 --> 01:34:46,362
The men that took you...

1028
01:34:46,465 --> 01:34:48,865
they're angry like that too.

1029
01:34:48,968 --> 01:34:51,129
Makes 'em mean.

1030
01:34:53,439 --> 01:34:55,964
You have to promise me, Zach,
that you won't be like them.

1031
01:34:56,075 --> 01:34:58,339
I don't want to.

1032
01:34:58,444 --> 01:35:00,969
Me either.

1033
01:35:27,172 --> 01:35:30,005
No way I'm not
becomin' a lawyer now.

1034
01:35:31,844 --> 01:35:34,972
I'm gonna be one of them drum majors
Dr. King talks about.

1035
01:35:35,080 --> 01:35:37,207
I know you will.

1036
01:35:37,316 --> 01:35:42,185
And... 10, maybe
15 years from now...

1037
01:35:43,455 --> 01:35:45,355
we'll be at your book signin'.

1038
01:36:03,575 --> 01:36:06,669
So don't forget our story, all right?

1039
01:36:08,647 --> 01:36:10,512
I won't.

1040
01:36:21,460 --> 01:36:25,226
<i>I have you know I am now a registered voter.</i>

1041
01:36:25,330 --> 01:36:27,525
- Really?
- I'll be castin' my vote for...

1042
01:36:27,633 --> 01:36:29,567
Lyndon Johnson and Hubert Humphrey.

1043
01:36:35,207 --> 01:36:37,368
I love you, Miss Rosaleen.

1044
01:36:51,690 --> 01:36:54,420
- Neil.
- Hello, ladies.

1045
01:37:12,711 --> 01:37:14,576
Hi.

1046
01:37:14,680 --> 01:37:17,547
Hi.

1047
01:37:17,649 --> 01:37:21,585
Didn't you call me here to talk?
I'm a little busy.

1048
01:37:21,687 --> 01:37:25,521
- You ain't the only one busy.
- I'm just supposed to stand here and watch how busy you are?

1049
01:37:25,624 --> 01:37:26,955
No.

1050
