I was wonderin' if you'd be
willin' to ask again.

1052
01:37:44,576 --> 01:37:46,771
Ask what?

1053
01:37:50,182 --> 01:37:52,275
This supposed to be funny?

1054
01:38:02,394 --> 01:38:05,022
June Boatwright, will you marry me?

1055
01:38:09,902 --> 01:38:11,802
Yes.

1056
01:38:11,904 --> 01:38:13,997
Yes?

1057
01:38:15,274 --> 01:38:17,174
Yes? Yes?

1058
01:38:17,276 --> 01:38:19,904
Yes.

1059
01:38:23,649 --> 01:38:26,743
She said yes.

1060
01:38:26,852 --> 01:38:29,013
- Oh, my God.
- Good for you.

1061
01:38:29,121 --> 01:38:31,112
Come on. We're goin' to
the jewelry store right now...

1062
01:38:31,223 --> 01:38:33,384
pickin' out a ring before you
change your mind, all right?

1063
01:38:33,492 --> 01:38:35,619
What? You don't already have one?

1064
01:38:35,727 --> 01:38:37,627
Girl, come on.

1065
01:38:37,729 --> 01:38:39,993
How come you don't have one?

1066
01:39:08,427 --> 01:39:11,885
Well, well, well.
Look who's here.

1067
01:39:14,733 --> 01:39:16,724
Won't you come in?

1068
01:39:23,041 --> 01:39:25,271
<i>Well, all right, goddamn it.</i>

1069
01:39:25,377 --> 01:39:29,143
<i>You wanna pretend
I'm making a social visit, we'll pretend.</i>

1070
01:39:29,248 --> 01:39:32,046
I'm gonna take you out of here nice and quiet
or kickin' and screamin'.

1071
01:39:32,150 --> 01:39:34,209
<i>Don't matter which one to me.</i>

1072
01:39:34,319 --> 01:39:36,287
Have a seat if you want to.

1073
01:39:49,968 --> 01:39:51,993
So you been here the whole time?

1074
01:39:53,205 --> 01:39:55,105
With colored women?

1075
01:39:55,207 --> 01:39:58,233
<i>- Jesus Christ.
- How'd you find me?</i>

1076
01:40:00,912 --> 01:40:03,642
That map on your wall.

1077
01:40:03,749 --> 01:40:05,910
Came here, started askin' around.

1078
01:40:06,018 --> 01:40:10,284
Some old lady secretary at the law office
was more than happy to fill me in.

1079
01:40:13,759 --> 01:40:17,092
- Where's Rosaleen?
- She took off a long time ago.

1080
01:40:35,580 --> 01:40:38,913
Where'd you get that?

1081
01:40:39,017 --> 01:40:41,315
- Miss August gave it to me.
- Don't you lie to me.

1082
01:40:42,421 --> 01:40:44,321
I'm not lyin'.

1083
01:40:44,423 --> 01:40:46,857
She said it belonged to my...

1084
01:40:50,095 --> 01:40:53,531
I gave that pin to your mama
on her 22nd birthday.

1085
01:40:55,500 --> 01:40:58,298
Now you tell me right now.

1086
01:40:58,403 --> 01:41:01,065
- How'd this August woman get it?
- You gave this to my mother?

1087
01:41:01,173 --> 01:41:03,141
- Answer me.
- You did?

1088
01:41:05,744 --> 01:41:08,736
This is where my mother came
when she ran away from us.

1089
01:41:09,881 --> 01:41:12,076
She was wearin' it
the day she got here.

1090
01:41:22,961 --> 01:41:26,055
Miss August used to take care of her
when she was a little girl.

1091
01:41:36,308 --> 01:41:39,038
I looked for her
everywhere I could think.

1092
01:41:41,146 --> 01:41:43,080
And she was right here.

1093
01:41:44,616 --> 01:41:47,084
Jesus Christ, she was right here.

1094
01:41:59,631 --> 01:42:02,464
Goddamn you, Deborah!

1095
01:42:02,567 --> 01:42:04,432
You ain't leavin' me again!

1096
01:42:04,536 --> 01:42:06,401
Get back here!

1097
01:42:06,505 --> 01:42:08,700
T. Ray, it's me, Lily!

1098
01:42:08,807 --> 01:42:10,798
Daddy!

1099
01:42:26,291 --> 01:42:29,351
You... You look like her.

1100
01:42:37,669 --> 01:42:40,934
My whole life's
been nothin' but a hole...

1101
01:42:41,039 --> 01:42:43,872
where my mother should've been.

1102
01:42:43,975 --> 01:42:46,170
It left me always achin'.

1103
01:42:48,280 --> 01:42:50,475
But I never thought about
what it did to you.

1104
01:42:59,558 --> 01:43:02,152
- We're goin' home.
- I'm stayin' here.

1105
01:43:05,430 --> 01:43:08,194
<i>You think I'm gonna
walk out ofhere and leave you?</i>

1106
01:43:08,300 --> 01:43:10,291
I don't even know these damn people.

1107
01:43:10,402 --> 01:43:12,302
I know them.

1108
01:43:13,472 --> 01:43:15,599
And August Boatwright
is a good person.

1109
01:43:15,707 --> 01:43:18,437
<i>Now, what makes you think
she'd even want you here?</i>

1110
01:43:18,543 --> 01:43:21,774
Lily can have a home here
as long as she wants.

1111
01:43:25,183 --> 01:43:27,048
Lily said you'd run off.

1112
01:43:27,152 --> 01:43:29,552
Well, I guess I'm back now.

1113
01:43:29,654 --> 01:43:34,114
<i>Well, I don't really care
where you end up...</i>

1114
01:43:35,327 --> 01:43:37,261
but Lily's comin' with me.

1115
01:43:45,303 --> 01:43:47,203
Everybody all right?

1116
01:43:48,773 --> 01:43:50,741
We all right.

1117
01:43:50,842 --> 01:43:52,867
This is Mr. Owens...

1118
01:43:52,978 --> 01:43:54,878
Lily's father.

1119
01:43:54,980 --> 01:43:57,471
He came here for a visit.

1120
01:44:00,652 --> 01:44:03,052
<i>Mr. Owens...</i>

1121
01:44:03,154 --> 01:44:08,091
you'd be doing Lily and us
a big favor by leavin' her here.

1122
01:44:08,193 --> 01:44:12,152
I made her my apprentice beekeeper.
She learnin' the whole business.

1123
01:44:15,200 --> 01:44:17,065
We love Lily.

1124
01:44:18,837 --> 01:44:21,738
<i>We'll get her started in school.</i>

1125
01:44:21,840 --> 01:44:25,173
We'll take care of her.
I promise you that.

1126
01:44:34,286 --> 01:44:36,345
Well...

1127
01:44:38,723 --> 01:44:40,623
good riddance.

1128
01:45:09,421 --> 01:45:12,117
<i>Stop! Stop!</i>

1129
01:45:16,995 --> 01:45:20,931
The day my mother died, you said
she was only comin' back for her things.

1130
01:45:22,334 --> 01:45:24,461
Is that true?

1131
01:45:27,305 --> 01:45:29,205
No.

1132
01:45:30,642 --> 01:45:33,167
No. She was comin' for you.

1133
01:45:37,048 --> 01:45:39,141
Why did you lie?

1134
01:45:42,520 --> 01:45:44,715
'Cause she didn't come for me.

1135
01:46:20,592 --> 01:46:24,585
<i>I still tell myself
that when T. Ray drove away that day...</i>

1136
01:46:24,696 --> 01:46:27,824
<i>he wasn't sayin: "Good riddance. "</i>

1137
01:46:27,932 --> 01:46:33,029
<i>He was sayin: "Lily, you are better off there
with all these mothers. "</i>

1138
01:46:34,406 --> 01:46:38,672
<i>I have more mothers than
any three girls off the street.</i>

1139
01:46:39,978 --> 01:46:42,173
<i>They are the moons
shinin'over me.</i>

1140
01:46:48,219 --> 01:46:50,449
<i>I guess I have forgiven myself.</i>

1141
01:46:50,555 --> 01:46:55,356
<i>Although sometimes in the night,
my dreams will take me back to sadness...</i>

1142
01:46:55,460 --> 01:46:59,260
<i>and I have to wake up and forgive again.</i>

1143
01:46:59,364 --> 01:47:02,390
<i>But Mary is always there.</i>

1144
01:47:03,868 --> 01:47:06,336
<i>I feel her at unexpected moments.</i>

1145
01:47:07,706 --> 01:47:09,901
<i>She will suddenly rise.</i>

1146
01:47:10,008 --> 01:47:14,843
<i>And when she does,
she does not go up into the sky...</i>

1147
01:47:14,946 --> 01:47:17,312
<i>but further inside of me.</i>

1148
